{
  "stem": "1857.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And while we're walking for about an hour on the streets, a little boy, about 15-year-old boy, walks by and says to us, [? 'Amhu?' ?]",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[? 'Amhu' ?] was like a code word.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Am-- you know what 'am' is in Hebrew, is 'nation.' [? 'Amhu' ?] means 'from the nation.' And whenever one Jew met another Jew, ask, [? 'Amhu?' ?] Are you from the nation?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said, [? 'Amhu,' ?] and I turned around.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he started speaking Yiddish to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he says, 'We want to go to Germany.' He says, 'Come with me.' And he took us to a basement, where there were about 14 people sitting.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were two Jews from Palestine, from the Bricha, who were smuggling people over the border to bring them to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's how we went over the border to Bavaria, in snow, New Year's Eve, 1945-1946.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that little boy was our leader through the border.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When he'd show like this, we stop or we go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we came to Bavaria.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We came to a city called Selb.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then I got on the train, and we went to Munich.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And from Munich, I went to a DP  camp-- displaced persons camp-- called Feldafing, where my uncle was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that's where I stayed after the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then they opened the university in Munich.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I made the exams.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I entered the engineering school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Besides that, I also got a job in camp, in the HIAS, in the Immigration Department.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And within a few months, I was in the Immigration Department.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I tried to immigrate myself and my parents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My parents came, too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we got the visa, American visa, New Year's-- Erev Rosh Hashanah, 1946.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
